cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper discusses video-based anomaly detection using deep learning techniques for video feature representation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised deep learning algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses action recognition, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also addresses the issue of false alarms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
